  "text": "Another element of child's preparation for anaesthesia is skin anaesthesia at the site of the puncture. EMLA cream or patch (60 minutes before puncture), Ametop gel or lidocaine gel under an occlusive dressing (30 minutes before puncture) could be used [CITATION_1] .",
